# Dynamic Routing using RIP â€“ Cisco Packet Tracer

This project demonstrates **dynamic routing** using **RIP (Routing Information Protocol)** in a simulated network topology built in **Cisco Packet Tracer**.

---

## ğŸ–¥ï¸ Topology Overview

![Topology](Dynamic%20Routing%20RIP.png)

The network consists of:
- **2 Routers** (Cisco 2911)
- **2 Switches**
- **6 PCs**
- **3 Networks:**
  - `198.168.2.0/24` â€“ Left LAN
  - `198.168.3.0/24` â€“ Right LAN
  - `198.168.1.0/24` â€“ Inter-router link

---

## âš™ï¸ Router Configuration (RIP)

### Router0 (Left Side)
```plaintext
enable
configure terminal
router rip
version 2
no auto-summary
network 198.168.1.0
network 198.168.2.0
exit




Router1 (Right Side)

enable
configure terminal
router rip
version 2
no auto-summary
network 198.168.1.0
network 198.168.3.0
exit


